&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;SRU has now relocated to Gillies. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the nursing team on Gillies (Specialist Receiving Unit).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are a passionate nurse looking to work in a diverse and stimulating environment, this is the place for you. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are an emergency admission unit that receives patients from four specialities within the Cancer and Associated Specialities Division: Oncology, Haematology, Renal and Infectious Diseases. The vast majority of our patients are patients with cancer that have become unwell during their treatment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;On SRU we pride ourselves on our Neutropenic Sepsis Care and Acute Care Skills. This is an excellent environment to develop and learn a plethora of clinical skills. You will be supported by our dedicated clinical educator, and the ward team throughout your practice on SRU. For us staff development is essential. As a member of our team you will have access to an Oncology Foundation Course, and a Haematology Study day to ensure you have the relevant specialist knowledge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;SRU is committed to consistent high standards of care for patients and this has been recognised by the numerous nominations and shortlisting to NUH Honours Awards and the successful improvement projects carried out by members of our team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a transformational team that is not afraid of change and we encourage our staff to bring forward ideas and initiatives to improve the care we provide for our patients and the working environment. SRU has an established Shared Governance Council that promotes positive changes for our patients and staff. We are also actively involved in the Magnet journey and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;are eager to hear from candidates who want to be part of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;delivering excellent patient outcomes and improving the job satisfaction of nurses at Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust (NUH).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are an enthusiastic, self-motivated nurse, that enjoys being part of a team then we would love to hear from you. If you have any questions or would like to arrange an informal visit, please contact the unit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
